Commentary Text: Sandeep Sharma to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Manish Pandey!! Now, now - this is simply sensational from Manish. He's had a shocker by his own high standards today, but he has pulled off an absolute ripper now. Kishan will consider himself desperately unlucky here, length ball and he flat-batted the lofted drive to the right of long-on. Had enough power, but not the elevation. Manish rushed across from long-on, threw himself at the ball - was parallel to the ground when he completed the two-handed catch and then had the sense to make sure that it didn't pop out when his elbow hit the ground. Ishan Kishan c Manish Pandey b Sandeep Sharma 31(23) [4s-1 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to de Kock, out Caught&Bowled!! A miscue from de Kock, Rashid called for the catch and Rashid takes the catch - running all the way to mid-wicket. The quicker delivery from the Afghan maestro - was the wrong 'un and de Kock didn't spot it, was setting himself for the pull and ended up playing against the turn. A massive top-edge and the ball was in the air for a long time. Rashid was always under the delivery, watches it keenly and takes it over his shoulder. End of a fine knowck from the MI opener. de Kock c and b Rashid Khan 67(39) [4s-4 6s-4]
